"{\"uid\": \"news18.com-movies-tom-cruise-to-perform-epic-stunt-at-paris-olympics-closing-ceremony-and-pass-torch-to-la-report-8989056.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"As part of the ceremony, Paris Mayor Anne Hidalgo will hand the Olympic flag to Los Angeles Mayor Karen Bass.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 109, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 25, \"end\": 36, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Mayor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 37, \"end\": 49, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}, {\"begin\": 80, \"end\": 91, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999815827, \"rank\": 1.2500698459381582e-11, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karen Bass\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a dramatic turn of events, Hollywood star Tom Cruise, 62 will rappel from the roof of the Stade de France to the field, flag in hand.\", \"from\": 110, \"to\": 246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 140, \"end\": 149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999936379072115, \"rank\": 3.575369104229514e-06, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 155, \"end\": 165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although there are rumors of a possible stunt double, the anticipation for Cruise's appearance is high.\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 350, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The broadcast will then shift to a pre-recorded segment where Cruise is shown flying from France to LA.\", \"from\": 352, \"to\": 455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 442, \"end\": 448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995833177859949, \"rank\": 0.0003235323280307506, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This will culminate in a skydiving stunt to the iconic Hollywood sign.\", \"from\": 456, \"to\": 526, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 511, \"end\": 525, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hollywood sign\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once on the ground, Cruise will hand the flag to athletes from various sports, including a cyclist, skateboarder, and volleyball player, who will then parade it around Los Angeles, the host city for the 2028 Games.\", \"from\": 527, \"to\": 741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 695, \"end\": 706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999815827, \"rank\": 1.2500698459381582e-11, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to TMZ, the filming for this segment took place in March.\", \"from\": 743, \"to\": 810, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Photos of Cruise descending the Hollywood sign circulated online, but the Olympic connection was not initially suspected.\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 932, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 843, \"end\": 857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hollywood sign\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TMZ also reported that Cruise was the mastermind behind this spectacle.\", \"from\": 934, \"to\": 1005, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He proposed the idea of linking the Paris and LA Games through a series of stunts to the International Olympic Committee.\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1127, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1042, \"end\": 1047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.595329500000981e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1095, \"end\": 1126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 Organizing Committee has kept the details of the ceremony under wraps.\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1133, \"end\": 1143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0875652236074295e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas Jolly, the artistic director for Paris 2024, aims to turn the Stade de France into a grand concert hall featuring over 100 performers.\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1356, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1215, \"end\": 1221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.8486162934715459, \"rank\": 0.17409921456115598, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}, {\"begin\": 1255, \"end\": 1265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0875652236074295e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1284, \"end\": 1299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly described the event as \\\"a very visual, very choreographic, very acrobatic show with an operatic dimension to give a great visual fresco and say goodbye to athletes from all over the world,\\\" promising a memorable celebration that honors both past and future.\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1620, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He continued, \\\"Together, let us make this evening a memorable and conscious celebration, honouring the past and embracing the future.\\\"\", \"from\": 1621, \"to\": 1755, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cruise, who carried the Olympic torch in LA in 2004, was seen attending women's gymnastics and swimming events during the first week of the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 1757, \"to\": 1909, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Representatives for Cruise have yet to respond to requests for comment.\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 1981, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Latest Blogs\", \"from\": 1983, \"to\": 1995, \"entities\": []}]}"